claim.claim-text:
1. A printing method using a server computer for a relay between one or more client computers and one or more printers that are connected to each other via a network, comprising the steps, executed by the server computer, of: 
receiving a printer secure communication session establishment request from a printer and establishing a printer secure communication session with the printer; 
receiving a client secure communication session establishment request from a client computer and establishing a client secure communication session with the client computer; 
receiving, from the client computer, a print job in which the printer is designated as an output destination printer; and 
sending the received print job to the printer as the output destination printer.

3. A printing method using a server computer for a relay between one or more client computers and one or more printers that are connected to each other via a network, comprising the steps, executed by the server computer, of: 
receiving one or more registration requests from the printers and managing, as usable printers, the printers that have sent the registration requests; 
receiving, from a client computer, a first secure communication session establishment request that is directed to an output destination printer that is one of the usable printers; 
sending, to the output destination printer, a request for sending a second secure communication session establishment request: 
receiving a second secure communication session establishment request that is sent from the output destination printer in response to the request from the server computer; 
establishing a secure communication session between the client computer and the output destination printer by connecting the first and second secure communication session establishment requests; and 
transferring, to the output destination printer with which the secure communication session has been established, a print job that is sent from the client computer.

13. A server computer for a relay between one or more client computers and one or more printers that are connected to each other via a network, the server computer comprising: 
a module for receiving one or more registration requests from the printers on the network and managing, as usable printers, the printers that have sent the registration requests: 
a module for receiving a printer secure communication session establishment request from a printer and establishing a secure communication session with the printer; 
a module for receiving a client secure communication session establishment request from a client computer and establishing a client secure communication session with the client computer; 
a module for receiving, from the client computer, a print job in which one of the usable printers is designated as an output destination printer; and 
a module for sending the received print job to the designated output destination printer.

14. A client computer being adopted to be connected to a printer via a server computer on a network, the client computer comprising: 
a module for asking the server computer about one or more usable printers and receiving a list of the usable printers from the server computer; 
a module for enabling a user to select an output destination printer from the usable printers in the received list; 
a module for generating print job data based on prescribed print subject data; and 
a module for sending the print job data to the server computer together with designation information indicating the output destination printer according to secure communication.

15. A server computer for a relay between one or more client computers and one or more printers that are connected to each other via a network, the server computer comprising: 
a module for receiving one or more registration requests from the printers on the network and managing, as usable printers, the printers that have sent the registration requests; 
a module for receiving, from a client computer, a first secure communication session establishment request that is directed to an output destination printer that is one of the usable printers; 
a module for sending, to the output destination printer, a request for sending a second secure communication session establishment request; 
a module for receiving the second secure communication session establishment request that is sent from the output destination printer in response to the request from the server computer; 
a module for establishing a secure communication session between the client computer and the output destination printer by connecting the first and second secure communication session establishment requests; and 
a module for transferring, to the output destination printer with which the secure communication session has been established, a print job that is sent from the client computer.

16. A printing method using a server computer for a relay between one or more client computers and one or more printers that are connected to each other via a network, comprising the steps, executed by the server computer, of: 
receiving one or more registration requests from the printers and managing, as usable printers, the printers that have sent the registration requests; 
receiving a first secure communication session establishment request from a client computer and establishing a first secure communication session with the client computer; 
sending, to an output destination printer that is one of the usable printers, a request for sending a second secure communication session establishment request; 
receiving a second secure communication session establishment request that is sent from the output destination printer in response to the request from the server computer, and establishing a second secure communication session with the output destination printer; and 
receiving a print job from the client computer and sending the received print job to the output destination printer.
